y to. I will proceed with these prompts.\n\n\n**Finalizing Email Parameters**\n\nI've determined that I need to gather two key pieces of information: Alex's email address and Cory's email address for the CC field. With these addresses, I can construct and send the email with the `agentmail` command via `exec`. The email will be sent from `orion_gatewaybot@agentmail.to` with the subject \"Late for meeting\" and the body \"I will be 10 minutes late to our 3pm meeting.\" I am prepared to prompt the user for this information now.\n\n\n**Confirming Core Information**\n\nI'm now certain about my next steps. I'll be requesting Alex's email address and Cory's email address. Once I have those crucial parameters, I can construct the appropriate `agentmail` command using the `exec` tool. I'll need to specify \"Late for meeting\" as the subject, and the message \"I will be 10 minutes late to our 3pm meeting.\" I am prepared to begin these prompts.\n\n\n**Formulating Prompt Questions**\n\nI'm now formulating the exact questions to get the required email addresses. I've considered that I need both Alex's and the user's email addresses to ensure I can successfully construct and send the email with the `agentmail` tool via `exec`, while also adhering to ORION's email policies. The wording needs to be clear and direct, to avoid any confusion.\n\n\n**Formulating Direct Questions**\n\nI'm now certain about my plan: I must ask the user for both Alex's email address and their own email address to use as the CC. I've re-evaluated all the relevant information and determined this is the most direct path forward. With those details in hand, I can create and execute the `agentmail` command using the `exec` tool. I'm now composing the questions.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>To send that email, I need Alex's email address and your email address for the CC. Can you please provide them?</final>","textSignature":""}],"api":"google-generative-ai","provider":"google","model":"gemini-2.5-fl